🚌 SMART BUS TRACKING & OVERCROWDING DETECTION SYSTEM
Project Proposal Document
1️⃣ Project Title

Smart Bus Tracking & Overcrowding Detection System Using IoT, AI & Real-Time Analytics

2️⃣ Introduction

Public and institutional transport systems often lack real-time monitoring of bus locations and passenger occupancy levels. Students and commuters face uncertainty regarding arrival times and frequently encounter overcrowded buses, leading to inconvenience and safety concerns.

This project proposes an intelligent transport monitoring system that integrates IoT devices, GPS tracking, AI-based passenger counting, and real-time analytics dashboards to improve transportation efficiency, safety, and management.

3️⃣ Problem Statement

Students face:

Uncertainty about bus arrival times

Long waiting periods

Unsafe overcrowded buses

Lack of transparency in bus capacity status

No real-time transport monitoring system

Transport administrators lack:

Live bus tracking

Passenger load analytics

Overcrowding alerts

Route optimization insights

4️⃣ Objectives

The main objectives of the project are:

Implement real-time GPS-based bus tracking

Develop automated passenger counting system

Detect and alert overcrowding situations

Provide a live dashboard for transport management

Offer a student-facing application to check bus status

Generate transport analytics for decision-making

Enable predictive arrival time estimation using AI

5️⃣ Scope of the Project

The system will be implemented for:

